Amphidial fovea relatively small, circular, 8 µm in diameter (25% of corresponding body diameter wide), situated at level of grouped subcephalic setae, about 18 µm from anterior end (
Figure 3C
).

Spicules paired, equal in length, but dissimilar in shape. Right spicule slender (
Figure 4C
), left one with large manubrium proximally (
Figure 4D
), 56 µm (1.2 a.b.d.) long. Gubernaculum bucket-shaped, with short dorsal apophysis (
Figure 3A
). Precloacal supplement absent. Anterior testis outstretched and situated to left of intestine; posterior testis reflexed and disposed to right of intestine.
